# Ignore fast-xml-parser vulnerability (AWS SDK transitive dependency)
# This is a DoS vulnerability in XML parsing that doesn't affect our use case
# AWS SDK team is working on updating their dependencies
# Tracking: https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-37qj-frw5-hhjh
audit-level=critical
# Expected peer-dependency warning: @xstate/react (pinned transitively by
# @aws-amplify/ui-react@^6.x as @xstate/react@^3.2.2) declares a React peer of
# ^16.8 || ^17 || ^18 and is tied to xstate v4. This project runs React 19, so
# npm prints a peer warning during install. It is cosmetic only:
#   - not a vulnerability, not a build/type-check/runtime error
#   - @xstate/react@3.2.2 uses only stable React hook APIs that work on React 19
#   - the latest Amplify (6.15.4) still pins @xstate/react@^3.2.2, so upgrading
#     Amplify does not resolve it, and bumping @xstate/react to 4.x/5.x pulls in
#     xstate v5 (breaking) and would break Amplify
# Accepted as upstream lag; it resolves when Amplify adopts xstate v5. Do NOT
# add legacy-peer-deps to silence it (that disables peer checks project-wide).
